[normal]Written evidence submitted by Roger A. [bold]Pielke[bold] [bold]Sr[bold] (IPC0011)[bold]Roger A. Pielke Sr. is currently a Senior Research Scientist in the Cooperative Institute for Research in Environmental Sciences (CIRES) and a Senior Research Associate at the University of Colorado-Boulder in the Department of Atmospheric and Oceanic Scie
[normal]nces (ATOC) at the University of Colorado in Boulder (November 2005 -present). He is also an Emeritus Professor of Atmospheric Science at Colorado State 
[normal]University
[normal]. 
[normal]Roger Pielke Sr. was elected a Fellow of the AMS in 1982 and a Fellow of the American Geoph
[normal]ysical Union in 2004
[normal].
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]He has
[normal] also
[normal] served as President of the American Association of State Climatologists
[normal] and as State Climatologist for Colorado
[normal].
[normal]Dr. Pielke has published over 370 papers in peer-reviewed journals, 55 chapters in books, co-edited 9 books, 
[normal]and made over 700 presentations during his career to date. A listing of papers can be viewed at the project website:
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]http://cires.colorado.edu/science/groups/pielke/pubs/
[normal].
